CatDescriptText: Mrs. Fannie Smith, laundry worker, 9 Jacksonia Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 31, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the District Attorney's office and the courts are exerting all out efforts in prosecuting equal rights cases in which Negroes are the victims?"  Answer reads: "I don't think so. Apparently, all they want to do is to talk and then dismiss the cases."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Fannie Smith, wearing plaid dress with light colored buttons, bow on chest, and light colored cardigan sweater, posed with hand on hip in front of painted brick wall
